"author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "````rust\r\npub fn fna(s: Option<String>) -> usize {\r\n     match s  {\r\n         Some(s) =>{ return s.len();},\r\n         None =>  {return 0; },\r\n     }\r\n\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\npub fn fnb(s: Option<String>) -> usize {\r\n     if let Some(s) = s {\r\n         return s.len();\r\n     } else {\r\n         return 0;\r\n     }\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\npub fn fnc(s: Option<String>) -> usize {\r\n      s.map(|x| x.len()).unwrap_or(0)\r\n}\r\n````\r\nhttps://rust.godbolt.org/z/cG3b9x\r\n\r\nAll these 3 functions do the same.\r\nFor the first two, llvm/rust realizes that they are identical and only saves one copy inside the binary, but for `fnc` this is not the case for some reason.\r\n`fnc` is saved separately although it generates the same instructions as `fna`/`fnb`\r\n\r\nhttps://rust.godbolt.org/z/Y6zazj", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/82817/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/82817/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}